# BMAD Method — Cursor Integration

## Agent personas (invoke via skills)

| Agent | Skill | When to use |
|-------|-------|-------------|
| Amelia (Dev) | `bmad-agent-dev` | Story implementation, TDD, code review, quick dev |
| Winston (Architect) | `bmad-agent-architect` | Architecture decisions, implementation readiness |
| John (PM) | `bmad-agent-pm` | PRDs, epics, stories |
| Mary (Analyst) | `bmad-agent-analyst` | Discovery, research |
| Sally (UX) | `bmad-agent-ux-designer` | UX design specs |

## Key workflows

- **Implement story**: `bmad-dev-story` (Amelia menu `DS`)
- **Quick fix/feature**: `bmad-quick-dev` (Amelia menu `QD`)
- **Create architecture**: `bmad-create-architecture` (Winston menu `CA`)
- **Readiness check**: `bmad-check-implementation-readiness` (Winston menu `IR`)
- **Unsure what next**: `bmad-help`

## Config

- BMAD config: `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`
- Team overrides: `_bmad/custom/*.toml`
- Skills live in `.agents/skills/` (symlinked to `.cursor/skills/`)

## Infrastructure skills

`docker-manage`, `postgres-manage`, `keycloak-manage`, `minio-manage`, `start-app` — use when working on dev environment or infra.
